main event: A woman in Wappingers Falls, New York saw a circular, white light object on multiple occasions since March 31, 1966.
interesting points: The object was the size of a pea held at arm's length and appeared to be a white light.
The object descended at a 45-degree angle and seemed to dive into the ground, disappearing below the horizon.
The witness had seen the same or similar objects at intervals since March 31, 1966.
On April 25, 1966, the witness saw an object about the size of a Volkswagen car at a range of 150 feet, and provided sketches of the object and its location.
The report mentions that the witness saw several red lights in the sky on various occasions, following smooth flight paths and changing attitudes, with multiple objects seen simultaneously.
